-- Irving Stitsky Gets 85-Year Sentence in $23 Million Real Estate Fraud Case
-- Bob Van Voris
-- 2010-07-06T17:15:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-06/irving-stitsky-gets-85-year-sentence-in-23-million-real-estate-fraud-case.html

          
          
             Irving Stitsky, who defrauded more
than 250 people in a $23 million fraudulent real estate
investment, was sentenced to 85 years in prison today in
Manhattan federal court. U.S. District Judge Kimba Wood
sentenced Stitsky, whom she called “an inveterate con man,” to
the maximum for his third securities fraud conviction.  
